{"word":"λιτή","slug":"λιτή","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>λιτή</b></el> <el>(λῐτή, ἡ,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:λίτομαι'><el>λίτομαι</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>a prayer, entreaty</i>, mostly in <a href='S:plural'>pl.</a>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><el>Λιταί</el>, <i>Prayers of sorrow and repentance</i>, personified in <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b> 9. 502 <a href='S:sequens'>sq.</a><p/></div>"}]}